In [[mathematics]], the '''Fontaine–Mazur conjectures''' are some conjectures introduced by {{harvs|txt|last1=Fontaine|author1-link=Jean-Marc Fontaine|last2=Mazur | author2-link=Barry Mazur|year=1995}} about when [[Galois module|''p''-adic representations]] of [[Galois group]]s of [[number field]]s can be constructed from representations on [[étale cohomology]] groups of a varieties.<ref>{{cite book|author=Koch, Helmut|authorlink=Helmut Koch (mathematician)|chapter=Fontaine-Mazur Conjecture|title=Galois theory of p-extensions|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|year=2013|page=180|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nqfvCAAAQBAJ&pg=PA180}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author=Calegari, Frank|title=Even Galois representations and the Fontaine–Mazur conjecture|journal=Inventiones Mathematicae|year=2011|volume=185|pages=1–16|url=http://www.math.uchicago.edu/~fcale/papers/EvenPotential.pdf|doi=10.1007/s00222-010-0297-0}} [http://arxiv.org/abs/0907.3427 arXiv preprint]</ref> Some cases of this conjecture in dimension 2 were already proved by {{harvtxt | Dieulefait | 2004}}.

