In [[category theory]], a branch of [[mathematics]], a '''Frobenius category''' is an [[exact category]] in which the notions of injective objects and projective objects coincide and there are enough injectives (or equivalently enough projectives). It is an analog of a [[Frobenius algebra]].
==Properties== The [[Stable module category|stable category]] of a Frobenius category is canonically a [[triangulated category]].
==See also== * [[Dagger compact category]] * [[Tannakian category]]
